author: HelloFresh
---

Wash and dry produce.

Trim and thinly slice @radishes{3}. Zest and quarter @lime{1}. Halve, peel, and thinly
slice @onion{1}. Drain @pineapple{4%oz}, reserving juice.

In a #small microwave-safe bowl{}, combine radishes, juice from half the lime,
¼ of the onion, and a big pinch of @salt{pinch}; cover with #plastic wrap{}.
Microwave until veggies are slightly pink, ~{30-45%seconds}.

In a separate #small bowl{}, combine @sour cream{1.5%tablespoon} with lime zest.
Add water 1 tsp at a time until mixture reaches a drizzling consistency. Season
with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{2%teaspoon} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat.
Add pineapple and season with salt and pepper. Cook, stirring, until browned
and caramelized, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Turn off heat; transfer to a #plate{}. Wipe out pan.

Heat a drizzle of oil in same pan over medium-high heat. Add remaining onion
and season with salt and pepper. Cook, stirring, until softened, ~{4-6%minutes}.

Add @diced chicken thighs{10%oz} and @Southwest spice blend{1%tablespoon}.
Cook, breaking up meat into pieces, until browned and cooked through,
~{4-6%minutes}.

Stir in @Tex-Mex paste{1}, caramelized pineapple, and reserved pineapple juice
until mixture is saucy and combined.

> Open package of chicken and drain off any excess liquid. Swap in chicken
> (no need to break up into pieces!) or beef for pork. Cook through
> remainder of step as instructed.

While pork cooks, wrap @flour tortillas{6} in damp #paper towels{} and microwave
until warm and pliable, ~{30%seconds}.

Divide tortillas between plates; fill with pork mixture, lime crema, and as many
pickled veggies (draining first) as you like. Pick @cilantro{0.25%oz}(leaves from
stems) leaves; tear leaves into pieces and sprinkle over tacos. Serve with any
remaining lime wedges on the side.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.